Description: This is a 1965 Teisco Del Ray Tulip electric guitar. Comes in the traditional tobacco sunburst finish. The instrument is in excellent condition and is fully functional. All the parts are original. The electronics work perfectly and are all original. 1965 is the first year where they offered the metal pickguard. The guitar has its original tremelo system and arm. Has a volume and tone on the pickguard. Cleaned and flushed pots and switches. Restrung it and oiled the finger board. Comes with a padded gig bag. Plays great for a 50 year old instrument! Great vintage round neck. This is a very nice instrument that is fun to play. Its all set up and ready to go! Some more information in the Tulip model of Teisco Del Ray guitars: TulipsTwo new models that would eventually become mainstays joined the Teisco line in ’65. Theye were two double cuts with slightly more flared horns, in a sort of tulip shape. Both had a single, wide, chrome-covered pickup with poles exposed along one edge. This was similar to the old MJ-1 but by ’65 would become the new SM series. Both had bolt-on necks with bound rosewood fretboards and the top-edge rectangular inlays. The E-100 had a bridge/tailpiece assembly, volume and tone on a small pickguard, and one of the elongated Strat-style heads. The ET-100 had a platform vibrato. As a sign of things to come, the Teisco Del Rey ET-100 had a regular Strat-style headstock, the first to appear on Teiscos, as far as I’m aware.Finishes shown in the ’65 Teisco Del Rey catalog included a black/brown tobacco sunburst, a fire-engine red and a metallic silver.
